[I] Find, verify, and analyze leaked credentials

[T] TruffleHog is the most powerful secrets Discovery, Classification,
[T] Validation, and Analysis tool. In this context secret refers to a
[T] credential a machine uses to authenticate itself to another machine. This
[T] includes API keys, database passwords, private encryption keys, and more.

[U] https://trufflesecurity.com/

[A] Truffle Security Co.
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/security
[F] CROSS

[L] AGPL
[V] 3.94.2

[D] 5b721586ca98b77fe6be9bc65cf3291df58c4f53691d5c83c165c1a8 trufflehog-3.94.2.tar.gz https://github.com/trufflesecurity/trufflehog/archive/v3.94.2/

. $base/package/*/*/go-conf.in
hook_add postmake 5 'install trufflehog $root$bindir/'
